# Project map & priorities for Cursor
IMPORTANT_PATHS:
- yalla_london/app/**
- yalla_london/components/**
- yalla_london/lib/**
- yalla_london/prisma/**
- yalla_london/scripts/**
- yalla_london/config/**
- docs/**
- vercel.json

PRIMARY_ENTRYPOINTS:
- yalla_london/app/app/layout.tsx
- yalla_london/app/app/page.tsx
- yalla_london/app/app/api/**/route.ts

INFRA:
- yalla_london/app/prisma/schema.prisma
- yalla_london/app/lib/supabase.ts
- yalla_london/app/vercel.json
- .env.local.example

STYLE GUIDELINES:
- TypeScript only, Next.js App Router conventions
- Server-first data fetching, isolated client components
- Keep env access through a single module
- No secrets in code or logs

DB CHANGES:
- Edit yalla_london/app/prisma/schema.prisma
- Run: pnpm prisma generate
- Provide migration instructions when needed

DEPLOYMENT:
- Use Vercel CLI (login via email magic link)
- Sync envs with `vercel env`

SECURITY:
- Never print real secrets
- Use `process.env` and `.env.local`

SUPABASE_USAGE:
- API routes: createServerClient({ cookies })
- Browser components: createBrowserClient()
- Scripts/cron: createServiceClient()
- Always check isSupabaseAvailable() before using

ENV_VARS_DETECTED:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- DATABASE_URL, DIRECT_URL, NEXTAUTH_SECRET, NEXTAUTH_URL
- AWS_*, OPENAI_API_KEY, ABACUSAI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_*
- FEATURE_* flags for Phase 4 features

